oai_dc:dc.dc:title: FLOW DEPENDENCY OF BOTTOMSTRESSES IN TIDAL MODELS
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Leendertse, Jan J.
Langerak, A.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: tidal model
flow dependency
bottom stress
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: In modeling studies the bottomstress parameter may not be taken as a constant for making predictions. This is particularly true when large changes are being made in the water bodies. Engineering judgement is than necessary as studies to a relation between the bottomstress parameter and tidal flow velocity are not conclusive.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 21 (1988): Proceedings of 21st Conference on Coastal Engineering, Torremolinos, Spain, 1988.; 200
